&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Summary:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the Director of Project Management, you will be the primary architect of SmithRx’s Operational Operating System. This is not a traditional &quot;admin&quot; PMO role; we are looking for a systems-thinking leader who can bridge the gap between complex roadmaps and executive-level strategic outcomes. You will evolve the Project Management function into a high-maturity, directive function that drives decision durability and portfolio integrity across the entire enterprise.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will design the governance frameworks that allow SmithRx to scale, leveraging Stage-Gate methodologies to ensure our most ambitious initiatives and migrations maintain the deterministic rigor required for healthcare and financial transactions. You will be the guardian of &quot;invisible work,&quot; advocating for operational stability and technical debt remediation as first-class citizens in our portfolio.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We need a leader who is versatile and driven, capable of translating 50+ concurrent workstreams into a singular, actionable executive narrative. You will display extreme ownership, identifying &quot;information dark spots&quot; and eliminating delivery bottlenecks before they impact our members. At SmithRx, you won&#39;t just track the roadmap; you will build the engine that executes it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you will do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;1. Governance &amp;amp; Stage-Gate Leadership&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the Lifecycle: Define and enforce a unified Stage-Gate process (e.g., Intake → Discovery → Alignment → Execution → Post-Launch).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Gatekeeping: Ensure clear entry/exit criteria and decision frameworks at each gate to minimize &quot;scope churn&quot; and rework.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strategic Mapping: Ensure every project in the portfolio is accurately mapped to Company OKRs with a robust risk mitigation plan.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Trade-off Analysis: Surface critical trade-offs regarding cost, timing, and complexity to enable senior leadership to make high-durability decisions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
