&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Summary:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Financial Analyst on the Account Management team, you will serve as the primary data subject matter expert (SME) and the strategic bridge between our client-facing teams and the Data Analysis/Reporting department. Your mission is to translate complex pharmacy benefit data into actionable financial insights for our clients. You will be a trusted advisor to both internal Account Management leadership and client financial teams, ensuring that every strategic decision is backed by rigorous analysis and a deep understanding of SmithRx financial components.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you will do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the resolution of complex client scenarios by conducting deep-dive data research and root-cause analysis.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with the account team to identify cost drivers, utilization shifts, and clinical opportunities within a client’s portfolio to recommend plan design changes that mitigate spend.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the primary liaison between Account Management and the Reporting/Data Analyst teams to ensure client reporting needs are technically feasible and strategically sound.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Interpret pharmacy claims data, trend analysis, and rebate projections to provide &quot;the story behind the numbers&quot; for client presentations and Quarterly Business Reviews (QBRs).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee the integrity of client-facing financial reports, ensuring data aligns with contractual obligations and client expectations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work on behalf of the Account Management team, collaborating with internal technical teams to improve automated reporting tools and identify product gaps based on client feedback and data limitations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assess financial data for indicators of client attrition risk and work with Account Managers to develop data-driven mitigation strategies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as a data mentor to Account Managers, coaching them on how to interpret financial metrics and present data-heavy slides effectively.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in existing and prospective client meetings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
